{
  "stem": "5275.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We stayed, most of the time, in the basement.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We didn't have any food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was eating Jello, [LAUGHS] which was in the form of hard-- I don't know how to call it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The kind of Jello that they had at that time, you had to put in the hot water and boil the hot water to make the Jello.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Well, I was taking an ax and cutting these little pieces of the Jello and eating it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That was about my-- my food for about at least a week.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The 25th of September was the worst night, in which the air bombardment was 12 hours from morning to evening.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the Warsaw was ablaze.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, the Polish Army gave up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Surrendered.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at that time, I-- that was the day I went back to my father because after the bombardment, I wanted to see whether he survived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so I left there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was fine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went to-- that-- that was on a Monday, Monday, the 25th of September.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went back to my father in the evening.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was fine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I stayed there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the next day, Tuesday, we suddenly saw the German planes flying over, very low.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we couldn't understand why.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, the radio told us that Warsaw had surrendered.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [CLEARS THROAT] then, [DRINKS WATER] we continued living at-- I continued living with my father and my stepmother.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was an-- [CLEARS THROAT] may I tell you a very interesting incident, though?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our-- our apartment was on the third floor, which was the upper floor of that apartment building.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was still during the war, during the 25 days that Warsaw was surrounded.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
